# Comprehensive A-Z Sorted & Chronological Device Catalog Select Plan

This plan details the implementation of a structured device catalog selection interface for smartphones, tablets, laptops, and smartwatches. It addresses the user's request to sort brands alphabetically (A-Z) and models chronologically (oldest to newest), and explains the constraints surrounding hardware auto-detection in modern browsers.

## User Review Required

### 1. Browser Hardware Auto-Detection Explanation & Limitations
> [!WARNING]
> **Why we cannot fully auto-detect the exact device model:**
> Modern web browsers (Chrome, Safari, Firefox, Edge) restrict access to specific hardware identification strings to protect user privacy (preventing "browser fingerprinting").
> - The `Navigator.userAgent` header is frozen/genericized (e.g. all iPhones report `Mozilla/5.0 (iPhone; CPU iPhone OS 15_0 like Mac OS X) AppleWebKit/605.1.15` without specifying if it is an iPhone X, 13, 14, 15, or 16).
> - There are no browser APIs to retrieve the precise manufacturer model name (like "Galaxy S24 Ultra" or "iPad Pro M4").
>
> **The Solution:**
> We pre-populate an exhaustive structured device catalog dropdown in the UI. To keep it highly user-friendly and flexible:
> 1. **Brands** are sorted alphabetically from **A to Z**.
> 2. **Models** under each brand are sorted in **chronological order** (oldest to newest/latest).
> 3. An **"Other / Custom Model"** option is provided at the bottom of the list. Clicking this dynamically displays a text input, allowing users to manually type their device name if it is not in the pre-populated list.

